text: Geestland is a town in Cuxhaven in Lower Saxony, Germany. It was created on 1 January 2015 by the merger of the former municipalities of Langen bei Bremerhaven, Bad Bederkesa, Drangstedt, Elmlohe, Flögeln, Köhlen, Kührstedt, Lintig and Ringstedt. == References == Category:2015 establishments in Europe Category:2010s establishments in Germany
title: Geestland
